Facility Description:



The Black Run Natural Gas Processing and Propane Distribution facility is located near the intersection of SR-16 and Black Run Road in western Muskingum County.  The facility is comprised of two separate operations:



1.    Natural gas processing to recover Butane and Natural Gasolines (BG).

2.    Bulk Propane storage and distribution to residential and commercial customers.



Natural Gas Processing



Natural gas is brought to the site via an underground natural gas pipeline where it is pumped through processing equipment that removes water and strips butane and natural gas liquids (BG) and propane from the natural gas.  The BG is comprised of approximately 30% Butane, 10% Propane and 60% Pentane.  The remaining natural gas is then sent back into the natural gas pipeline distribution system.  



The processing equipment is comprised of the following:



?    Natural gas fired engine to run the compressors;

?    Compressors push both natural gas and propane refrigerant through the process equipment;

?    Glycol dehydration process removes water vapor from the natural gas;

?    Chilling equipment liquefies the BG and propane;

?    Stabilizer Tower boils off the ethane;

?    Depropanizer equipment boils off propane and BG and then cools them and sends them to the bulk BG tank and bulk propane tank.  



The BG is stored in an onsite 25,000 gallon aboveground storage tank and sold to commercial reprocessing operations.  The propane is first stored in an onsite 18,000 gallon aboveground storage tank.  The propane can either be transferred to the other propane bulk tanks on site or can be loaded directly onto bobtail trucks for delivery to residential or commercial propane customers.



